# Task file conventions

When editing files under `01-ideas/`, `02-specs/`, `03-ready/`, or `04-shipped/`:

- Keep YAML frontmatter in sync: `title`, `domain`, `stage`, `created`. `stage` must match the folder.
- Preserve the `## Sign-offs` section (immediately after the title). Never delete old sign-off lines.
- Do not invent file moves between stages outside the `advance-task` procedure in `AGENTS.md` (ideasâ†’specs, specsâ†’ready) or a post-implementation ship to `04-shipped/` with `## Outcome`.
- Stop short of implementation detail in `02-specs/`; put concrete paths/schemas/verification in `03-ready/`.
